      <file>.claude/patterns/webresource/full-page-custom-page.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read SprkChat.tsx">
      Open `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChat.tsx`.
      Locate the `disabled={isStreaming || !session || isSessionLoading}` expression on the
      `SprkChatInput` (or whatever the Input element is named). Note the surrounding context
      and how `session` / `isSessionLoading` flow from `useChatSession`.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Survey consumers">
      Grep the repository for `&lt;SprkChat` usages to confirm no consumer is depending on the
      previous "disabled when no session" behavior as a feature. If any consumer is, surface
      it before changing — possibly add a prop to opt-out. Otherwise, proceed with the
      unconditional change per FR-06.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Modify disabled condition">
      Change `disabled={isStreaming || !session || isSessionLoading}` to `disabled={isStreaming}`.
      Leave all other input behaviors untouched (Enter to send, Shift+Enter for newline,
      placeholder text, accessibility labels).
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Verify lazy session creation path">
      Trace the `onSend` handler. Confirm that `useChatSession` already creates a session
      on first send if `session` is null. If not, add a guard at the start of `onSend`:
      `if (!session) { await createSession(); }`. (Most likely already in place.)
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Add unit test or update existing">
      In the SprkChat test suite, add (or update) a test: "input is editable on cold load
      with no session". Mock `useChatSession` to return `{ session: null, isSessionLoading: false }`;
      assert the Input is not disabled. Add a second test: "first send creates session and
      sends message" — mock `createSession` and `sendMessage`, simulate type + Enter, assert
      both are called in order.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Build + verify">
      Run `npm run build` against the shared library and against SpaarkeAi. Smoke in Vite
      dev: cold load → input is editable; type a message + Enter → message sends and AI
      response streams. No regression in active-streaming behavior (input disabled while
      streaming).
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read SprkChat.tsx + useChatSession to understand the lazy path</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Modify the disabled expression</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Survey SprkChat consumers across the repo</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">Run `npm test` and `npm run build` to validate</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChat.tsx</output>
    <output type="test">Updated unit tests for SprkChat (input editable on cold load + lazy session creation on first send)</output>
    <output type="report">Task completion report citing the disabled-condition diff and the consumer survey result</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`SprkChat.tsx` no longer disables the input on `!session` or `isSessionLoading`; only `isStreaming` remains in the disabled condition.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Unit test "input editable on cold load" passes (mock `session: null`).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Unit test "first send creates session then sends" passes (lazy creation verified).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Manual smoke in Vite dev: cold load → input editable; type + Enter → session created + message sent + AI replies.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Active-streaming UX preserved: input remains disabled while `isStreaming === true`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build` succeeds for both `@spaarke/ui-components` and SpaarkeAi.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Consumer survey confirms no breaking-change impact (or, if any, surfaced and resolved with an opt-out prop).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="cold load editable (FR-06)">
      Open SpaarkeAi welcome state. Verify the chat input is NOT visibly disabled; cursor
      can enter; typing works; placeholder text reads naturally.
    </test>
    <test name="lazy session creation on first send">
      Type "hello" + Enter on cold load. Verify (a) BFF call to create a session, then
      (b) message-send call, then (c) streamed AI response. No "Session not ready" error.
    </test>
    <test name="streaming disable preserved">
      During an in-flight stream, verify the input becomes disabled (visually muted, no
      keyboard input accepted). After stream completes, input re-enables.
    </test>
    <test name="dark-mode compliance (NFR-06, ADR-021)">
      Toggle dark mode. Verify input disabled/enabled visual states use Fluent v9 tokens
      correctly — no hex literals introduced.
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

